HEADWORD: Thionic
<hw>Thi*on"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ brimstone,
sulphur.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to sulphur;
containing or resembling sulphur; specifically, designating certain of
the thio compounds; <as>as, the <ex>thionic</ex> acids</as>. Cf.
<er>Dithionic</er>, <er>Trithionic</er>, <er>Tetrathionic</er>,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thionine</ent>⟦br⟧
